<font color="#FF0000">WINDOW OF OPPORTUNITY NARROWS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan 25 12:52:24 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
We will never be successful annihilating a nation that we have no intention of occupying.  To occupy we will always be the infidels and invaders and as such will continue a holy war for all eternity.  A process that neither we nor any other nation of a so-called civilized culture has been willing to endure.<br><br>
Are we willing to sacrifice our lives and dedicate them to the battle so intensely like the holy warriors of the region?  Hold funerals before we enter battle because we have no intention of returning alive.  The threat of death is no deterrent.<br><br>
It requires surgical precision to eliminate the offending targets and to ensure that we take out those who orchestrate this insanity.  The enemy who understands that they can be touched at any time will hesitate, even a religious zealot.  Hurt the heart, show they he can be touched whenever we please.  Make it personal.  Killing his people to punish him has no effect except to give him more support from those who waiver.  We always attack a nation when we are at odds with a few.  It has never worked effectively and will not now.<br><br>
To annihilate this nation would require the use of nuclear weapons and the collateral damage is unacceptable.  To leave it crippled will give the lead to Iran who can and will be the next threat of the region.<br><br>
Iraq understands terror.  They must be allowed to look in its face and understand we can and will deliver.  A lesson to those other area powers to remember.  No one is willing to unleash the darkness upon their nation.<br><br>
It is not always what we do to an enemy but the thought of what they are convinced we are willing to do.  We have not done that yet.  We flexed our muscles and scorched his extremities, but we have not visited the nest.  It is time we did so or stop making noise.  The longer we continue with our current course of action the less chance we will have of success.<br><br>
If he is allowed to achieve his weapons he will not hesitate to hold the world hostage with the same threats, but only after he shows us he is willing to use them.  Israel, Iran, Turkey, Kuwait or worse a US city, which do we wish to lose before we are convinced we must shed these restraints of civilization and deal with the problem.<br>

